The course provides an overview of the most common psychiatric disorders in the adult population, discusses possible problems and peculiarities in the physiotherapeutic treatment of patients with mental disorders, and learns to apply various therapeutic techniques used in physiotherapy in the treatment of patients with mental disorders.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide students with knowledge and practical skills for working in physiotherapy with psychiatrically ill patients.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student: 1. Knows the most common psychiatric disorders among adults and their main symptoms; 2. Is able to recognize a patient with psychiatric disorder and takes into account possible peculiarities when communicating with him; 3. Analyzes possible obstacles occurring during therapy process with psychiatric patients and is able to find solutions; 4. Implements a variety of therapies used within mental health physiotherapy and general treatment principles to treat patients with psychiatric disorder
